{"type":"message","id":"46cea8e7","parentId":"c7333c1e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:01:44.679Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Telegram gateway timeout is still happening. The previous heartbeat-state.json already noted this as a blocker. This is the same \"gateway timeout\" issue.\n\nSo the change is detected (QLHV group back to running), but the Telegram delivery is blocked by the gateway timeout. \n\nI should still report this internally - the change was detected, but the delivery failed. The task says to compose the report to group -5163901258, but the delivery is blocked.\n\nLet me update the heartbeat-state.json to reflect the current state and note the blocked delivery.\n\nActually, per the instructions: \"Return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\" - but since the delivery is blocked by the gateway timeout, the summary will be delivered through the cron response.\n \nThe cron job spawns a subagent that runs every 5 minutes, and the instructions say to return a plain text summary that gets delivered automatically - though in this case the delivery is blocked by the gateway timeout, so the summary will come through the cron response instead. I should update heartbeat-state.json to track this state, then output the summary as requested.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the cron:6f3323ef session is just this current session running, so it's not a new change. The real changes are the QLHV group returning to running status and the gateway timeout preventing delivery. I should update the state file and provide the summary output, but I need to clarify whether outputting the summary here will actually reach the group or if it's just part of the response flow.","thinkingSignature":"5d52eb9208f8aa5102b3667af4e5a9c725a88e48cb0ed795aff76abae7e832f5"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway timeout persists — same blocker noted in heartbeat-state.json. Updating state and reporting the detected change.\n"},{"type":